> If source properties are used to modify the compiler flags for specific source files rather than for a whole target, changing the sourceâ€™s compiler flags will still result in all of the targetâ€™s sources being rebuilt, not just the affected source file.

I don't think that applies here.  The source's compile flags are never changed between builds: `sha256_avx2.cpp` is either compiled with `${AVX2_CXXFLAGS}`, or it is not compiled at all. And `AVX2_CXXFLAGS` is only ever set to `-mavx -mavx2`. The issue that all of the libraries source files get recompiled never occurs.

@hebasto, can you elaborate why you think the source-specific compile options are hard to reason about?
